(a) In the event of Purchase by Seller:

If the Seller elects to make a purchase, it shall be incumbent upon them to:

1. Fulfill all obligations and conditions specified in this Agreement, or as may be subsequently agreed upon in writing by both parties;
2. Assure the quality, authenticity, and integrity of the goods being purchased, guaranteeing their conformity with any applicable specifications or standards;
3. Bear all risks associated with the purchased goods, including but not limited to loss, theft, or damage, from the point of transfer until they are delivered and accepted;
4. Provide Buyer with a complete and accurate bill of sale, detailing all relevant terms, conditions, and costs;
5. Resolve any disputes or claims arising out of the purchase within a reasonable timeframe, in good faith and in accordance with this Agreement or applicable laws.

Should Seller fail to comply with any of the above obligations, Buyer shall have the right to:

1. Terminate this Agreement and seek damages;
2. Pursue legal remedies against Seller for breach of contract or other applicable causes of action;
3. Retain any funds paid to Seller in connection with the purchase until the dispute is resolved satisfactorily.
